I"Ý<p>If <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/phenomenal-space-is-adaptive">continuous experience is a trajectory in phenomenal space</a>, and if often <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/mental-representations-connect-internal-with-external-state">mental representations are called forth to enable phenomenal representations, without external influences</a>, and if <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/categorical-perception-translates-in-a-blindspot-for-nuance">categorical perception and concepts</a> are a thing, then trying to <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/visual-imagery-brightness-modulates-pupil-size">imagine</a> a gradient of experience should be met with a series of discontinuities.</p>
